Close Brace 5 Minute React: Testing with Jest

  ---------
  Resources
  ---------

  Benefits of TDD (Test-Driven Development) - James Sinclair: 
    http://jrsinclair.com/articles/2016/one-weird-trick-that-will-change-the-way-you-code-forever-javascript-tdd/


  ------------
  Install Jest
  ------------

    $ yarn add jest --dev  // the --dev wont be installed on a production build

    Install supertest to test HTTP responses (is API responding correctly?)

      $ yarn add supertest --dev

  -------------
  Writing Tests
  -------------

    Write test first, then write routine to make it pass

      Add user to DB

        $ mongo 
        > use dbName

        > db.users.deletyMany({});  // clear out users collection if needed

        > db.users.insert({ "username": "administrator", "password": "changethisasap", "firstName": "Joshua", "lastName":"Mullenberg"});

        

